special vote
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a vote cast at a parliamentary election otherwise than at a polling place in the voter's own electorate on election day, by a voter whose name is on a printed electoral roll.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: Jim Cameron writes : the term was introduced in 1956 (now Electoral Act 1993) and includes votes cast before polling day, overseas votes and votes at polling places outside the home electorate. Similar arrangemnents in other countries appear to have different names. Also special (elliptical)
